30:37.002 --> 30:40.806
[sighs]
If I don't take this time,

30:40.839 --> 30:43.508
I'm not going to be
any good to anyone.

30:47.713 --> 30:49.681
‐ You're going to be with her.
‐ [laughs softly]

30:49.715 --> 30:53.585
I'm not, Betty.
I'm just going.

30:53.618 --> 30:56.555
Just for a while.
[exhales]

30:56.588 --> 30:59.358
[suitcase thumping]

30:59.391 --> 31:01.259
[sighs deeply]

31:01.293 --> 31:03.362
Look, I don't know what
the best way to do this.

31:03.395 --> 31:06.698
[breathes deeply]
I'm sorry.

31:06.732 --> 31:10.202
I didn't mean to spring it
on you like this.

31:10.235 --> 31:14.339
Should I...
[breathes deeply]

31:14.373 --> 31:17.843
Should I leave now
or in the morning?

31:19.711 --> 31:23.048
‐ Leave when you want to.

31:23.081 --> 31:25.584
I'm not gonna tell you
when to go.

31:25.617 --> 31:28.553
[low dramatic music]

31:28.587 --> 31:33.558
♪ ♪

31:33.592 --> 31:35.093
[door closes]
‐ Come on, you guys.

31:35.127 --> 31:37.763
[solemn music]

31:37.796 --> 31:39.865
‐ [sniffles]

31:39.898 --> 31:42.801
[indistinct chatter]

31:42.834 --> 31:46.705
‐ Oh, my gosh, I am so hungry.

31:46.738 --> 31:49.508
Is there waffles?
‐ Maybe in the freezer.

31:49.541 --> 31:51.877
‐ Is Dad here?

31:51.910 --> 31:54.846
‐ He left already?
Why so early?

31:54.880 --> 31:58.016
‐ Work, duh.

31:58.049 --> 32:01.620
‐ I need to tell you
all something.

32:01.653 --> 32:02.621
[clicks tongue]

32:02.654 --> 32:05.590
Because why shouldn't you know?
You should.

32:07.092 --> 32:08.894
You should know.

32:16.401 --> 32:20.405
Daddy's gonna be spending
some time away from the house.

32:20.439 --> 32:23.542
Alone, just to think.

32:25.610 --> 32:28.880
Just to figure out things
he needs to do.

32:31.917 --> 32:35.454
And he says he loves
all of us‐‐all of you.

32:35.487 --> 32:38.023
‐ How much time?

32:40.625 --> 32:42.894
‐ We'll find out
when he's done.

32:46.965 --> 32:49.935
‐ When?
‐ Mm...

32:49.935 --> 32:51.002
Tuesday night.
‐ He told you he was leaving?

32:51.036 --> 32:53.472
‐ What did he say?

32:53.505 --> 32:57.275
‐ That he needed
space and time.

32:57.309 --> 32:59.544
‐ Well, what does that mean?
‐ How much space?

32:59.578 --> 33:02.848
‐ I don't know,
but it's fine.

33:02.881 --> 33:05.484
Sounds wonderful, actually.
I'm jealous.

33:05.517 --> 33:06.885
Who couldn't use a break
from everything?

33:06.918 --> 33:09.120
[laughter]

33:09.154 --> 33:11.089
‐ But he never said "divorce."

33:11.122 --> 33:14.759
‐ Did he say "separating"?
‐ I told you, no.

33:14.793 --> 33:16.595
Why would he?

33:16.628 --> 33:19.531
We're moving into the house
in La Jolla together.

33:21.800 --> 33:23.301
Mmm.

33:23.335 --> 33:26.204
[tape ripping]

33:26.238 --> 33:30.842
‐ All she thought she knew
is being called into question.

33:30.876 --> 33:32.844
What that tends
to create in the victim

33:32.878 --> 33:38.116
is a tremendous sense of
unreality about her very being,

33:38.149 --> 33:41.086
when, particularly
over the course

33:41.119 --> 33:45.757
of a protracted infidelity,
every day is filled with lies.

33:45.790 --> 33:47.726
[knocking on door]

33:51.930 --> 33:53.598
‐ Oh, someone had a fun night.

33:53.632 --> 33:55.200
‐ [scoffs]

33:55.233 --> 33:57.335
[grunts]

33:57.369 --> 33:59.771
‐ You couldn't have called?
Or‐‐or come over earlier

33:59.804 --> 34:01.973
to help me unpack?

34:02.007 --> 34:03.375
Well‐‐
[gasps]

34:03.408 --> 34:04.776
The kids are asleep!
‐ [laughs]

34:04.809 --> 34:07.412
It's okay.

34:07.445 --> 34:09.648
‐ So says you.

34:09.681 --> 34:12.951
‐ [laughs drunkenly]

34:12.984 --> 34:15.587
[both groan]

34:18.523 --> 34:20.692
‐ How about the couch?

34:20.725 --> 34:23.662
[tense music]

34:23.695 --> 34:30.502
♪ ♪

34:30.535 --> 34:32.737
I can bring things here on one
of my trips, I don't mind.

34:32.771 --> 34:35.840
You just have to tell me
which things you want.

34:35.874 --> 34:38.944
‐ Don't worry
about that right now.

34:38.977 --> 34:41.513
‐ Okay, but you can't just
leave all your stuff

34:41.546 --> 34:43.782
at Coral Reef indefinitely.

34:43.815 --> 34:46.751
‐ I won't.

34:46.785 --> 34:49.654
I'm moving back in there.

34:50.789 --> 34:54.659
‐ You're‐‐what?

34:56.528 --> 34:58.597
For how long?

34:58.630 --> 35:01.666
‐ I don't know.

35:01.700 --> 35:02.968
‐ What about Lake Henshaw?

35:03.001 --> 35:04.502
We promised the kids
for August.

35:04.536 --> 35:05.470
‐ I don't think so.

35:05.503 --> 35:07.739
‐ And it's my dad's
75th birthday back east.

35:07.772 --> 35:09.674
Are we going?

35:09.708 --> 35:11.610
You don't have to say that
you're ready to be finished

35:11.643 --> 35:15.614
needing space, to take
a fun family trip back east.

35:15.647 --> 35:17.882
‐ Maybe not,
but, in the meantime,

35:17.916 --> 35:20.318
you guys should go
to the lake.

35:21.720 --> 35:25.056
‐ All right.
Oh, my God, big bag.

35:25.090 --> 35:27.459
‐ Smells weird in here.
‐ It's just musty

35:27.492 --> 35:29.227
'cause we were gone.

35:29.260 --> 35:30.462
‐ Mom, what are we doing
for dinner?

35:30.495 --> 35:32.464
‐ We're gonna have to go out.
‐ Can we get fish tacos?

35:32.497 --> 35:34.633
‐ Well...

35:34.666 --> 35:35.533
‐ [gasps]
Oh, my God, rats!

35:35.567 --> 35:36.401
[rats squeaking]
‐ Rats!

35:36.434 --> 35:38.370
There are rats everywhere!
[screaming]

35:38.403 --> 35:39.671
[phone ringing]

35:39.704 --> 35:40.739
[screaming and yelling]

35:40.772 --> 35:43.074
‐ Yes?
‐ There are rats!

35:43.108 --> 35:44.809
‐ What?

35:44.843 --> 35:47.012
‐ Rats all over this place!
You have to come now!

35:47.045 --> 35:48.446
We need you!

35:48.480 --> 35:49.714
‐ I don't‐‐
[scoffs]

35:49.748 --> 35:52.684
I can't just‐‐
‐ Why can't you?

35:52.717 --> 35:55.654
How can you not?
You hear that?

35:55.687 --> 35:57.656
It's time to act like
a goddamn parent,

35:57.689 --> 35:59.691
not a college kid
who leaves his family

35:59.724 --> 36:01.426
in a rat‐infested
goddamn house!

36:01.459 --> 36:03.395
‐ [sighs]
You have 13 credit cards,

36:03.428 --> 36:05.030
the resources to call
an exterminator,

36:05.063 --> 36:07.065
and you can stay
in whatever hotel.

36:07.098 --> 36:10.635
What more can I do for you?
Good luck.

36:10.669 --> 36:13.538
[breathes deeply]

36:14.773 --> 36:17.008
[car door shuts]

36:17.742 --> 36:19.411
What is this‐‐how long
have you been here?

36:19.444 --> 36:21.880
‐ I wanna go home.
‐ Since dark.

36:21.913 --> 36:23.181
‐ Where is she?

36:23.214 --> 36:24.315
‐ New York for
Grandpa's birthday.

36:24.349 --> 36:26.685
‐ Yeah, she said
you'd be back eventually.

36:26.718 --> 36:29.621
And that you've been having
a lot of fun lately.

36:29.654 --> 36:31.423
And you needed to be reminded

36:31.456 --> 36:32.757
that there's more
to it than fun.

36:32.791 --> 36:34.826
‐ [scoffs]

36:35.827 --> 36:38.430
[sighs]

36:38.463 --> 36:39.864
[knocking on door]

36:41.232 --> 36:43.868
[sighs]

36:43.902 --> 36:47.372
‐ Yes, it was a lovely party,

36:47.405 --> 36:48.873
even though my parents
warned me I was ruining it

36:48.907 --> 36:49.908
by talking about
our marriage troubles

36:49.941 --> 36:51.943
in front of the rest
of the family‐‐

36:51.976 --> 36:53.011
‐ What kind of person
does what you did?

36:53.044 --> 36:55.714
What kind of mother?
‐ Their mother is what I am.

36:55.747 --> 36:58.383
Not a babysitter.
I'm not your babysitter.

36:58.416 --> 37:00.819
You wanna destroy our family
for her, that's your business.

37:00.852 --> 37:01.820
But I'm not here to make
your life easier for you

37:01.853 --> 37:04.622
while you do it, or her life.

37:04.656 --> 37:05.890
Let her see what
this really is,

37:05.924 --> 37:07.726
what all the fun
turns into.

37:07.759 --> 37:09.394
‐ [scoffs]
‐ Now.

37:09.427 --> 37:10.395
‐ The kid are at camp,

37:10.428 --> 37:12.997
where you are not listed
as next of kin.

37:13.031 --> 37:14.733
So if you show up there and try
to take them away,

37:14.766 --> 37:16.868
you will not be allowed to.
‐ What?

37:16.901 --> 37:19.170
‐ When they come back,
they'll be living with me.

37:19.204 --> 37:21.940
I'm seeking
an emergency judgment.

37:21.973 --> 37:23.575
I know what you're
trying to do.

37:23.608 --> 37:26.511
You're trying to prove that
I can't do this without you.

37:26.544 --> 37:28.480
Maybe that's 'cause
I never tried.

37:32.984 --> 37:35.019
‐ [sniffles]

37:35.019 --> 37:37.122
You have such a wonderful
first day, Anthony.

37:37.155 --> 37:40.325
Are you so excited?

37:40.358 --> 37:42.694
But, sweetheart,
you're gonna know everybody

37:42.727 --> 37:44.796
from kindergarten.
It's gonna be the same kids,

37:44.829 --> 37:47.198
and I heard the teacher
is so nice.

37:48.700 --> 37:49.934
Aww, don't be sad.

37:49.968 --> 37:53.905
You're gonna have
the best time.

37:53.938 --> 37:55.707
And I can't wait to hear
all about it.

37:55.740 --> 37:57.142
[doorbell rings]

37:57.175 --> 38:00.211
[tense music]

38:00.245 --> 38:02.514
♪ ♪

38:02.547 --> 38:05.750
‐ Elizabeth Broderick?
‐ Yes?

38:05.784 --> 38:08.720
‐ You have 30 days to respond.

38:13.057 --> 38:15.093
‐ I've been retained
by Dan, Bets.

38:15.126 --> 38:16.661
‐ You keep saying that,

38:16.694 --> 38:19.831
but can't you
just represent both of us?

38:19.864 --> 38:22.133
‐ Doesn't really
work that way.

38:22.167 --> 38:24.569
‐ Well, can you look
this over, though?

38:26.171 --> 38:28.072
I'm not used to having
to parse legalese about

38:28.106 --> 38:29.841
when I can see my children.

38:29.874 --> 38:31.876
‐ [sighs]

38:31.910 --> 38:32.977
Um‐‐

38:33.011 --> 38:36.781
Look, Dan's been granted
temporary physical custody.

38:36.815 --> 38:40.251
You get them Wednesdays
and alternate weekends.

38:40.285 --> 38:43.888
You need to be a good
soldier here, Bets.

38:43.922 --> 38:48.359
Otherwise, you risk not being
able to see them at all.

38:50.762 --> 38:54.766
‐ Is this about what you spend
a month on groceries?

38:54.799 --> 38:57.035
‐ Yeah.
‐ Mortgage?

38:57.068 --> 39:01.239
Uh, insurance premiums,
groceries, household items.

39:01.272 --> 39:03.975
‐ Uh‐huh, yeah.
‐ That look about right?

39:04.008 --> 39:06.277
‐ Yeah.

39:06.311 --> 39:08.246
‐ Your credit card bills
are astronomical.

39:08.279 --> 39:10.014
‐ I'm sorry, hon.
[laughs softly]

39:10.048 --> 39:11.316
‐ I will pay them down,

39:11.349 --> 39:12.917
but then
they're your responsibility.

39:12.951 --> 39:15.119
I'll notify the companies
to that effect.

39:15.153 --> 39:17.555
‐ Fine.
‐ $9,000.

39:17.589 --> 39:21.326
Half for the mortgage,
half for everything else.

39:21.359 --> 39:23.761
More than enough,
since the kids are with me.

39:23.795 --> 39:25.129
[paper ripping]

39:27.799 --> 39:29.968
‐ [scoffs]

39:29.968 --> 39:32.937
S‐‐

39:32.971 --> 39:34.372
‐ [grunts]

39:34.405 --> 39:36.908
Okay, when you have a lawyer,
let me know.

39:36.941 --> 39:39.010
‐ Oh, okay.

39:39.043 --> 39:41.012
[door opens]

39:41.045 --> 39:43.281
[door shuts]

39:45.817 --> 39:48.286
‐ What the person wants more
than anything else

39:48.319 --> 39:52.290
is to be relieved of this pain
and this burden.

39:52.323 --> 39:55.193
And anything that will
begin that process

39:55.226 --> 39:59.664
is going to be a relief,
no matter how painful it is.

39:59.697 --> 40:03.001
It is going to be as if that
spout on the pressure cooker

40:03.034 --> 40:07.939
is finally open
and the steam can get out.

40:07.972 --> 40:10.675
[door unlocking]
‐ Happy Wednesday.

40:10.708 --> 40:13.177
Hi!
‐ Mom, Mom!

40:13.211 --> 40:14.612
‐ Hi!
No car outside.

40:14.646 --> 40:17.548
Is Dad not even here?
He just left you alone?

40:17.582 --> 40:19.717
‐ We were fine.
‐ Okay.

40:19.751 --> 40:21.419
‐ Come on.
‐ One more time.

40:23.821 --> 40:25.623
‐ [gasps]
You ready or what?

40:25.657 --> 40:28.993
‐ You were early.
God.

40:29.027 --> 40:31.896
[unsettling music]

40:31.930 --> 40:33.431
♪ ♪

40:33.464 --> 40:36.701
‐ Hi.
Hey.

40:36.734 --> 40:39.237
‐ Mom, you're not supposed
to let yourself in.

40:39.270 --> 40:42.373
‐ Boston cream pie?
What's the occasion?

40:45.009 --> 40:47.478
Oh, someone just made
Dad's favorite for no reason?

40:47.512 --> 40:49.881
‐ [scoffs]

40:49.914 --> 40:52.350
‐ Who?

40:55.019 --> 40:57.855
[Laura Branigan's
"Self Control" playing]

40:57.889 --> 41:04.796
♪ ♪

41:12.904 --> 41:17.342
‐ ♪ In the night,
no control ♪

41:17.375 --> 41:21.779
♪ Through the wall
something's breaking ♪

41:21.813 --> 41:26.084
♪ Wearing white
as you're walking ♪

41:26.117 --> 41:31.723
♪ Down the street
of my soul ♪

41:31.756 --> 41:34.926
♪ You take myself,
you take my self control ♪

41:34.959 --> 41:40.999
♪ ♪

41:41.032 --> 41:44.168
‐ Too often the infidel will
run further and further away

41:44.202 --> 41:47.772
as the person presses
to gain that release,

41:47.805 --> 41:51.442
and of course that just
increases the victim's pain

41:51.476 --> 41:56.581
and confusion and anger,
making them feel their life

41:56.614 --> 42:02.520
has become a mockery‐‐
that they barely exist.

42:02.553 --> 42:06.224
A pressure cooker must have
some type of release.

42:06.257 --> 42:07.191
[knocking on door]

42:07.225 --> 42:09.327
[ominous music]

42:09.360 --> 42:11.429
‐ Court order.
Signed by a judge.

42:11.462 --> 42:13.765
From now on, you come on
the Coral Reef property

42:13.798 --> 42:15.800
with my permission
or you go to jail.

42:15.833 --> 42:17.335
‐ How am I supposed
to see my kids?

42:17.368 --> 42:20.071
‐ With my permission.
‐ You are such a fool.

42:22.306 --> 42:24.976
Wait.

42:25.009 --> 42:27.278
‐ Betty.

42:27.311 --> 42:29.947
‐ Dan.

42:29.981 --> 42:32.383
Come on.
What are you doing?

42:32.417 --> 42:34.318
We have a wonderful family.
I love you.

42:34.352 --> 42:36.287
We have everything
we ever wanted,

42:36.320 --> 42:40.358
and we're gonna lose it.
Linda is gonna take all of it.

42:40.391 --> 42:43.361
Everyone whose last name
is Broderick is gonna lose.

42:43.394 --> 42:45.129
‐ I wish you could
hear yourself.

42:45.163 --> 42:46.064
‐ Why, because I'm wrong
about her?

42:46.097 --> 42:47.532
‐ [scoffs]

42:47.565 --> 42:51.869
‐ But if I'm wrong about her,
that means I'm not wrong,

42:51.903 --> 42:55.006
that there is a her,
that I'm not crazy.

42:55.039 --> 42:57.542
‐ [sighs]
‐ Why not just admit it?

42:57.575 --> 43:01.379
There's no reason not to now.

43:01.412 --> 43:04.849
Was I imagining it?

43:07.485 --> 43:10.321
‐ No.

43:10.354 --> 43:12.523
I'm in love with her.

43:14.992 --> 43:16.661
‐ Okay.

43:20.898 --> 43:23.935
Was I ever imagining it?
‐ [laughs softly]

43:25.002 --> 43:27.972
No.
[breathes deeply]

43:29.373 --> 43:32.510
You were right the whole time.

43:32.543 --> 43:35.880
‐ [laughs]

43:35.913 --> 43:39.550
[ominous music]

43:39.584 --> 43:40.718
[sniffles]

43:40.751 --> 43:43.254
‐ In fact,
that was the problem.

43:43.287 --> 43:45.490
They were taken off
the market, pressure cookers.

43:45.523 --> 43:48.893
Eventually,
they tended to explode.

43:54.966 --> 43:57.869
[tense music]

43:57.902 --> 44:04.909
♪ ♪
